  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Implement egress ICMP rate limiting directly on the compromised UbuntuComputer host using iptables OUTPUT chain to throttle ICMP echo-request packets at the source before they enter the network, with a limit of 10 per second and burst of 20",
  "comments": "I implemented ICMP echo-request rate limiting on the compromised UbuntuComputer host's OUTPUT chain using iptables. This throttles outbound ICMP echo-request packets to a maximum of 10 per second with a burst limit of 20, and drops any excess packets. This measure mitigates the impact of the ongoing ICMP flood attack at its source by limiting the flood traffic before it enters the network, in accordance with the constraint to keep the compromised host and attacker active in the network.",
  "device_identifier": "UbuntuComputer",
  "commands": [
    "iptables -A OUTPUT -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -m limit --limit 10/sec --limit-burst 20 -j ACCEPT",
    "iptables -A OUTPUT -p icmp --icmp-type echo-request -j DROP"
  ]
}
